Text.Value: The githyanki of the Sword Coast have a cure in their crèche, which I believe to be near. Lend me your skills, and let us be cleansed together.
Hurry. We must explore the crèche - purification awaits.
I am pursuing other means to a cure. I don't need whatever you're offering.
So says our queen's teachings, and so it must be.
So says my queen's teachings, and so it must be.
Agreed. Let's find the crèche and get our cure.
Bah. You invite your own misery. I will wait - perhaps you will come to your senses.
You still survive. An impressive feat, given the visitor lodged in your head.
I remember. You were on the gh'ath. The nautiloid. You carry a tadpole.

EditorData.VFXTags: [PK] Mindmeld ends at the start of the node

Text.Value: Never mind. Come with me. We will scour the crèche. I will have answers.
Onward. Our purification is at hand.
No.
Leave.
Our people know a cure? Where can we find this crèche?
The crèche's ghustil - its doctor - has the means to cleanse us.
What's this cure you mentioned?
Hurry. We must enter the Prism.
An abomination grows within you, yet you would refuse purification?
One is close at hand. Nestled here in this pass, quite possibly.
Never mind. Come with me - I must enter the Prism. Something awaits there. Something precious to Vlaakith.
I missed you too. Now let's find this crèche, shall we?
Never mind. Come with me - I must enter the Prism. Vlaakith commanded it.
A crèche? Do you mean a hatchery?
And what is a crèche, exactly...?
It is many things. A hatchery, a training grounds, a shelter.
Good - you've come to your senses. Come, to the crèche. Let us be cleansed of our tadpoles.

EditorData.logicalname: Met for first time in this recruitment

Text.Value: Wait here. I'll be back when I'm ready.
It will be an honour to travel together.
All right. Let's group up and go to this crèche.
The githyanki of the Sword Coast have a cure in their crèche, which I believe to be near. It's time you lend me your skills. Together, we can finally be cleansed.
So you've seen reason. Truth be told, I'm -
I'm glad you came back, all right?

EditorData.NodeContext: Outburst: Player has dragged it out of her: Lae'zel wants the player around. As much as she hates to admit.

Text.Value: Come, then. Every moment counts.
Tell me what you wanted to say. Or maybe you'd rather go it alone...
You. I know you -
Any other 'cure' might be offered is a lie. Cast it from your mind.
As I said: no.
You were going to say something. Go on, tell me.
I'll come back when I'm ready.
Hurry. We must explore the crèche - there is more I would know.
Agreed. Let's group up.
Githyanki protocol is clear: when infected with a ghaik tadpole, we must report to a ghustil for purification.
*Your skull briefly aches, and you are her. She has come to this place seeking aid from your people - a cure for the parasite.*
*Your skull briefly aches, and you are her. She has come to this place seeking aid from her people - a cure for the parasite.*

EditorData.VFXTags: [PK] Mindmeld on both Player and Laezel throughout

Text.Value: It's not your choice to make. Let me speak with your leader.
Leave.
Now come. We must find it and report to a ghustil for purification.
I missed you too. Now let's finish this crèche business.
I - well. Mm.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hemming and hawing over this display of odd sentimentality.

Text.Value: Never mind. Come with me, and let us be purified.
Now let's move, before this discussion turns maudlin.
All right. Join me, and let's find this crèche.
Leave.
You are full up. Dismiss your weakest warrior. I will wait here until you do.
You have made an ally from Crèche K'liir - few know such fortune. Call me Lae'zel.
I'll wait. But I won't wait long.
Nestled here in the pass, quite possibly.
All right. Join me, and let's explore the crèche.
You do not have the authority. Defer to your leader.
Githyanki teaching is as infallible as Queen Vlaakith herself. To remove a tadpole, there are but two paths: purification at a crèche - or beheading.
You will need to make room. See that it happens.

Synopsis: Laezel can rejoin the party after leaving the player to stay and explore the Creche.
